      "term": "rezeroing",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C1",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "The act of setting an instrument, device, or weapon sight back to a correct zero point after it has changed.",
          "examples": [
            "After changing the rifle scope, she spent the afternoon rezeroing it at the range.",
            "Rezeroing of the pressure sensor is required whenever the readings start to drift."[1][2]
